You're correct! To display both integers and strings in the ListView, it makes sense to use a single list, converting integers to strings as needed. This simplifies the code and makes it easier to manage.

Here’s how you can modify the code to use a single `ArrayList<String>` and add both integers (as strings) and other strings to it.

### Updated MainActivity Code
```java
import android.os.Bundle;
import android.view.View;
import android.widget.ArrayAdapter;
import android.widget.Button;
import android.widget.ListView;

import androidx.appcompat.app.AppCompatActivity;

import java.util.ArrayList;

public class MainActivity extends AppCompatActivity {

    private ListView listView;
    private Button addButton;

    // Using a single ArrayList to hold Strings
    private ArrayList<String> items = new ArrayList<>();

    @Override
    protected void onCreate(Bundle savedInstanceState) {
        super.onCreate(savedInstanceState);
        setContentView(R.layout.activity_main);

        listView = findViewById(R.id.list_view);
        addButton = findViewById(R.id.add_button);

        // Set up ListView adapter
        final ArrayAdapter<String> adapter = new ArrayAdapter<>(this, android.R.layout.simple_list_item_1, items);
        listView.setAdapter(adapter);

        // Add items to ArrayList when button is clicked
        addButton.setOnClickListener(new View.OnClickListener() {
            int count = 1; // Counter for integers

            @Override
            public void onClick(View v) {
                // Add integer string and a regular string
                items.add("Item " + count);
                items.add(String.valueOf(count)); // Convert integer to string
                count++;

                // Notify adapter to refresh ListView
                adapter.notifyDataSetChanged();
            }
        });
    }
}
```

### Explanation
- **Single List**: We have one `ArrayList<String> items` to hold all entries, which now includes both strings and integer values converted to strings.
- **Counter for Items**: There's an integer counter that increments with each button click, adding a new item and its string representation.
- **Display Logic**: Both the strings and the integer representations are added to the same list, allowing the ListView to display them seamlessly.

