### Fetching Real-Time Exchange Rate:

To fetch the latest rate, you can use libraries like `HttpClient` to access an API. Here’s an example using an imaginary API:

```java
import java.io.*;
import java.net.*;
import org.json.JSONObject;

public class CurrencyConverter {
    public static void main(String[] args) throws Exception {
        String url = "https://api.exchangerate-api.com/v4/latest/USD"; // Example API URL
        URL obj = new URL(url);
        HttpURLConnection con = (HttpURLConnection) obj.openConnection();
        con.setRequestMethod("GET");

        BufferedReader in = new BufferedReader(new InputStreamReader(con.getInputStream()));
        String inputLine;
        StringBuffer response = new StringBuffer();

        while ((inputLine = in.readLine()) != null) {
            response.append(inputLine);
        }
        in.close();

        JSONObject json = new JSONObject(response.toString());
        double exchangeRate = json.getJSONObject("rates").getDouble("EUR");

        double dollars = 100; // Example amount
        double euros = dollars * exchangeRate;
        System.out.println(dollars + " dollars is " + euros + " euros.");
    }
}
```

